reviews.text: The name & location, just off Caine Rd, was intriguing.. hence I entered. The coffee was delicious though I wished it was warmer! Scone was cold & dense, though tasty.. in all the experience could have been better. But no regrets! The people who serve are v hospitable and friendly.. makes up for everything..not to mention that it's a respite from the climb to mid levels!!
Order butter coffee . Something special for me . Worth trying . Great  comfy place
Had an Affogato and a turkey cranberry toasty, both are amazing. The coffee was really rich and smooth, definitely worth coming over just for the coffee if you're in Central
Very nice and cosy coffee and juice shop right next to Central Escalator. Good and friendly staff. Outdoor area to sit as well.

Friendly and fast service. Nice banana bread. Tried both the iced latte and soy flat white. Both excellent with attention paid to presentation. Highly recommended, don't forget the nice outdoor seating area.
